news.title: Over 6,100 building licences approved in 2023: Coimbatore corporation
news.para: According to corporation officials, the civic body received as many as 8,668 building license applications last year. Of this, 6,123 were approved while 2,197 were rejected.

news.title: Gujarat: Rs 1,000 crore jantri push to stamp duty collection
news.para: In its annual budget, government has estimated that it will earn Rs 13,950 crore from stamp duty and registration fees in 2023-24.

news.title: Delhi: MCD to launch modified module of Sahbhagita Scheme to provide incentive to RWAs
news.para: Under the modified module of Sahbhagita Scheme, 10 per cent incentive will be given to RWAs/GHSs on the condition that at least 90 per cent of their residents have paid property tax, it said.

news.title: Delhi civic body hikes property rent in 79 markets by up to 10 times
news.para: "The enhancement of the ground rent may be followed on the similar lines as adopted by L&DO,” stated the public notice issued by the administrative officer, land and estate department on Monday.

news.title: Madras HC quashes Tamil Nadu's guideline value hike for property registration
news.para: Citing procedural infirmities, Justice P Velmurugan set aside the circular, saying that though government had the authority to increase the guideline value, it had to be done as per the procedure contemplated under the rules, which mandate constitution of an expert committee and public hearing before implementing the hike.

news.title: Two new FIRs allege forgery and conspiracy by HDIL promoter & staff in slum redevelopment
news.para: ​Bandra Kurla Complex (BKC) police registered the case on court's order based on the complaint filed before it by the two hutments--Fariuddin Shaikh (68) from Bharat Nagar and Hamidabano Shaikh (55) from Maharashtra Nagar (both in Bandra East).

news.title: Hansoge Enterprises sells 175-room hotel in Bengaluru for Rs 150 crore
news.para: According to industry estimates, around 59 hotels comprising 4,669 keys were signed by multiple hotel operators in the third quarter of 2023. In that quarter, the average daily rate rose 15.6% from a year earlier, resulting in a 15.1% increase in revenue per available room.

news.title: DDA's two-day live e-auction for 2,093 flats begins
news.para: The authority has received earnest money deposit (EMD) from 3,055 applicants who will be participating in the exercise. EMD is the booking amount deposited by people when they apply for flats after registration.

news.title: Income tax demand of Rs 4,000 crore looms over Shree Cement
news.para: The Income tax department conducted a survey on the company in June 2023 in connection with the deductions claimed under section 80IA of the Income Tax Act for the April 2014 to March 2023 period.

news.title: ED searches Chennai-based R R Group promoter in PMLA case
news.para: Raman, the ED alleged, funnelled the funds received from the group (Old Lane) in the form of FDI for the development of a tech park in Ambattur.

news.title: Indian-origin builder charged with perpetuating USD 93 million fraud scheme
news.para: The SEC announced that it obtained an asset freeze and other emergency relief concerning the alleged USD 93 million real estate investment fraud perpetrated by Kapoor.

news.title: ED gets custody of Ornate Spaces' MD accused of duping several flat buyers
news.para: Accused of cheating several flat buyers, he was arrested by the probe agency on Wednesday under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA). Special PMLA judge M G Deshpande, while remanding him in ED custody, noted that money laundering was a serious offence.

news.title: Land titling act not in force yet, Andhra Pradesh government tells HC
news.para: Advocate general S Sriram sought the high court’s directions to lower courts to not reject petitions arising out of land disputes as the new legislations have not come into force yet.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body collects property tax of Rs 465.7 crore in nine months of FY24
news.para: ​Property tax is one of the major source of revenue for the NMMC. Navi Mumbai is a major industrial belt in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region.

news.title: Delhi: MCD undertakes 37 demolition, 19 sealing actions following revocation of GRAP-III
news.para: ​Demolition actions were suspended after the enforcement of Graded Response Action Plan-III in December last year and were revoked on Monday following visible improvement in Delhi's air quality.

news.title: Changes in Chandigarh housing board building rules a major headache for allottees
news.para: ​The CHB need-based policies allowed for some types of constructions and designs in the houses. Following this, the allottees claim they constructed as per the changed guidelines.

news.title: Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar: Home owners not verifying tenant info on police radar
news.para: A police officer said that during the verification process it was found that the home owners in both the cases gave their apartments to seven Sudan nationals each.

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra reduces home loan rates by 15bps
news.para: Bank of Maharashtra will offer home loans at 8.35% as against 8.5% earlier. The bank has also waived off its processing fee on home loans, a statement said.

news.title: Kerala government amends housing scheme guidelines for fisherfolk
news.para: The money will be granted to those beneficiaries who have their own land 200 metres outside the high-tide zone, but presently reside within 50 metres from the high-tide line.
